<TEXT>
a man who wanted to have his wisdom 
teeth pulled was mistakenly given a lethal dose of a local 
anesthetic authorities said 
rodney scott craig 25 of san bernardino died saturday two 
days after he was given an overdose of lidocaine jim beisner 
chief deputy coroner of orange county said wednesday 
investigators said an unknown person in the office of oral 
surgeon chris larson mistakenly inserted intravenous lines into 
craigs arm that contained lidocaine instead of glucose a sugar 
solution used to raise blood sugar level 
beisner said he did not know how much lidocaine craig received 
before the mistake was discovered by larson or his staff garden 
grove police sgt phil mason said the coroner determined there was 
no criminal wrongdoing 
the california board of dental examiners was investigating the 
death said supervising investigator larry ballard 
