i did recommend danny quayle for the national guard 
phillippi said i just called the military department and said 
heres a good man you ought to take him it was just as i 
have done for many young men over many years i was just a peon 
calling the military department i had no power 
there was some disagreement over whether there were long waiting 
lists to get into the national guard in indiana as in other 
states 
john s anderson adjutant general prior to 1969 said one did 
exist but john n owens who followed anderson in the job said 
indiana units had vacancies galore 
quayle a hardliner on defense matters joined the national 
guard in 1969 when he had graduated from college and thus lost his 
student deferment from the draft quayle was a private first class 
in the guard serving as a writer in a public information unit 
until 1975 
few guard units were activated and sent to vietnam and many 
young men sought to join the guard to avoid being drafted and sent 
to vietnam of the more than 58000 american casualties in the 
vietnam war 97 were guardsmen in mobilized units 
phillippi said quayle inquired as to whether he might be sent to 
vietnam as part of a guard unit 
