<TEXT>
elaborate bonding rituals tribal chants 
ceremonial plumage a center spread in last months national 
geographic 
no its an anthropologistseye view of the republican national 
convention 
in other societies you usually just get together and kill a 
lot of pigs says martha ward a professor at the university of 
new orleans 
in america men in dark suits and women in red white and blue 
dresses travel long distances to attend meetings discuss issues 
and give speeches 
but wait 
people also stage feasts wear costumes and extoll their 
virtues be they cooperation loyalty defense aggression or 
careful spending habits and they do this all over the world in 
the pacific in africa in the united states 
the convention was classic anthropological drama says ward 
who viewed the spectacle on tv she watched swaying figures in 
funny hats and saw elaborately costumed primitive dancers she 
listened to delegates shout usa usa and heard echoes of 
ancient tribal chants 
rituals of this kind transcend ordinary bureaucratic 
actions she says we could get together and just nominate the 
guy its been done already anyhow but its important to have 
rituals of connection ceremonies achieve many purposes and most 
of what happens is very predictable 
gerald fords presence ancestorworship says ward they 
have to pay homage to ancestors they may rehabilitate one every 
now and then and drag out his bones jimmy carter got rehabbed for 
the democrats gerald ford was brought out by the republicans 
stressing connections to the past serves a purpose it gives 
us a chance to discuss our values to say these values are still 
important theyve seen us through tough times in the past and 
theyre good values for the future 
opening and closing prayers theres always a mild 
supernatural element of worship regardless of whether it offends 
is constitutional or sectarian its going to be there its very 
important that god bless the endeavor that you make it known hes 
on your side 
campaign hats and buttons are just so many tribal tattoos 
when youre in a transitional period or celebrating something 
its customary to alter your appearance we do it for weddings for 
funerals for graduations similar costumes reinforce unity 
they want these people to move as a group 
the daily communal breakfasts lunches and dinners are integral 
to the proceedings nothing happens in human society without 
food 
while most convention speeches contain little besides rhetoric 
the speakers choice of imagery can speak volumes ward says this 
year brought less sports and battle imagery and more feminine 
themes home and hearth 
every person talked about their families and paraded them out 
at great length 
there was no shortage of tough talk directed at democrats 
however ward calls that chestbeating its lockerroom stuff 
theyre patting these delegates on the rear end and sending them 
out there to win its very contagious what happens in groups you 
cant do this to yourself at home 
what happened this week in new orleans has nothing to do with 
survival with eating or sleeping or feeding your kids or even 
with whether the country runs or not it was pageantry plain and 
simple its a colossal game thats why its held in the 
superdome 
if the convention was a winner the rituals will work their 
magic 
people will go home feeling involved and committed says 
ward theyll work hard for their leaders best of all theyll 
contribute money labor pigs seashells 
