<TEXT>
a new elementary school in one of the nations 
most criticized school systems will reinvent the wheel its 
founder says by using corporatestyle management to boost learning 
like they do profits 
the school dedicated thursday has gained the blessing and the 
backing of such giants of capitalism as mcdonalds corp and united 
airlines 
its a compelling plan to educate young people not only in 
chicago but across the country mcdonalds spokeswoman stephanie 
skurdy said after the dedication of the corporatecommunity school 
on the citys west side 
the school will be run like a business meaning that if 
principal elaine c mosley a former elementary school principal in 
suburban oak park is unable to produce a superior product 
students she could be replaced said joe kellman the schools 
founder 
the tuitionfree school slated to begin classes sept 6 with 
150 students and seven teachers is being subsidized by almost 
three dozen sponsors 
sixteen of the corporations raised 2 million of the 3 million 
needed to run the school for three years officials said the 
annual cost is about 4100 per student about the same as the cost 
to educate public school students 
its a model project hopeful for urban reform in school 
programs said elaine younglove spokeswoman for another sponsor 
united airlines which has pledged 300000 in support over a 
threeyear period mcdonalds has given 75000 
we thought it was an opportunity theres a high dropout 
rate in chicago and thats one of our personal concerns getting 
that dropout rate down she said thursday night 
