<TEXT>
israel dealt a strong blow to the palestinian 
rebellion in the occupied lands outlawing arab popular committees 
and threatening their members and supporters with arrest and 
10year jail terms 
popular committees are grassroots organizations carrying out 
the directives of the uprisings underground leadership organizing 
demonstrations and patrols and supplying food and medical aid to 
the needy 
the decision to outlaw them came amid a twoday general strike 
launched in the west bank on thursday to protest israels policy of 
deporting arab activists the strike orders were passed around the 
west bank by masked youths many of whom shouted their message on 
loudspeakers 
palestinian protesters clashed with israeli troops throughout 
the occupied lands thursday leaving 11 arabs wounded red cross 
and hospital officials in the gaza strip said soldiers beat and 
clubbed more than 250 palestinians 
a threeday curfew in the gaza strip ended thursday but 180000 
arabs in 11 refugee camps and neighborhoods remained confined to 
their homes in addition 85000 west bank palestinians from nine 
villages and camps were under curfew 
defense minister yitzhak rabin said his decision to outlaw the 
popular committees would create legal means of dealing with the 
activists of the palestinian uprising 
but this is a formal judicial step that does not abolish the 
need to capture arrest put on trial or deport these people 
he said on israel radio 
the defense ministry said every palestinian who continues to be 
a member of the committees or assist them would be arrested and put 
on trial 
the committees stage underground classes in case of school 
closure by the israeli authorities they gather donations for 
families of the uprisings martyrs arab prisoners or those who 
who lost their jobs in israel during the 8monthold rebellion 
palestinians appeared enraged by rabins decision 
khanan ashrawi a lecturer at bir zeit university in the west 
bank said the step was only an excuse for further escalation 
the essence of the committees is that theyre popular they 
are trying to strike at all the palestinians in that case they 
will deport everybody its definitely a policy and its a ruthless 
policy she told the associated press 
meanwhile representatives of the european community lodged a 
protest with the foreign ministry expressing grave concern 
over the deportations ministry spokesman alon liel said delegates 
from spain greece and germany were told deportations were 
necessary to maintain law and order he said 
the foreign ministry also said it was checking allegations in a 
16page amnesty international report claiming israeli troops have 
beaten thousands of arabs since the uprising began in december the 
ministry said the londonbased human rights group conferred with 
biased sources 
