the hostage drama that ended thursday left three 
people dead and a host of questions about police handling of the 
episode here is a reconstruction of the twoday odyssey based on 
interviews with the gunmen and victims official accounts and media 
reports 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
silke bischof smiling faintly despite 
a loaded revolver pointed at her chest says shes all right but 
afraid police will act suddenly to end her hostage nightmare and 
somebody will be killed again 
two hours later the blond teenager whose face was flashed 
across the worlds tv screens and newspapers is dead a bandit has 
shot her through the heart during a final gunbattle with police on 
a crowded highway near the west german capital 
the bizarre 54hour drama begins when two gunmen with long 
criminal records storm a branch of the deutsche bank in the 
northwestern town of gladbeck barricading themselves inside and 
taking two hostages 
sure the situation is tense one of the gunmen tells local 
radio station ffn in a telephone interview at 2 pm tuesday about 
six hours after the siege has begun 
asked what will happen if authorities dont give in to their 
demands for money and a getaway car the gunman says then well 
all have to die 
the gunmen hansjuergen roesner 31 and dieter degowski 32 
are shabbily dressed and covered with tattoos they appear to have 
been taking drugs or drinking 
late in the evening after a day of failed police attempts to 
free the hostages the bandits scoop up 227000 shove their two 
hostages into an audi sedan provided by authorities and drive away 
for two hours police chase them through the ruhr industrial 
area they commandeer a bmw and police lose them somewhere along 
the way the bandits pick up female accomplice marion irma 
loeblich 34 they vanish until the next day 
late wednesday afternoon the bandits reach the northern port 
city of bremen about 55 miles southwest of hamburg during a 
shooting spree in a vegetable market they commandeer a city bus 
and take about 30 passengers as captives 
after about 15 minutes four elderly passangers and one young 
child leave the bus 
i simply stood up no one stopped me said konrad 
hofrichter an 83yearold retiree one elderly woman gets off and 
simply walks across the platform to catch a trolley home 
west germanys ard television network twice interrupts its 
evening newscast with bulletins on the unfolding events tv viewers 
see no police near the hijacked bus 
meanwhile the three bandits walk around with guns in hand 
chatting with reporters and occasionally gazing into the sky at a 
police helicopter monitoring them 
inside 15yearold emanuele de giorgi sits with his arm around 
his little sister and silke bischof sits bolt upright and stares 
both will soon be dead 
negotiations with police break down roesner brings out a young 
girl holds a pistol to her head and threatens to shoot if the 
bandits demands for a fast getaway car arent met 
around 10 pm the bus takes off with about 25 hostages 
sparking a police chase that leaves one policeman dead in a car 
wreck 
late wednesday evening the bus pulls up to a rest stop on the 
autobahn or highway near bremen to get food and alcohol the two 
hostages from the bank in gladbeck are released 
i kept hoping i would be freed but i also had to figure there 
were good chances id simply get shot down says andrea blecker 
a 23yearold customer service representative 
as the gunmens accomplice ms loeblich comes out from a brief 
trip to the rest stop toilet brandishing a cocked pistol police 
jump her and throw her to the ground 
roesner and degowski seek a victim to force her release and 
emanuele de giorgi reacts 
emanuele threw himself in front of his sister to protect 
her said one shaken witness who declined to be identified 
one of the gunmen believed to be degowski pumps three bullets 
into emanuele and walks away from the dying youth whose italian 
parents had come to germany in search of a better life 
ambulance ambulance the waiting journalists shriek as the 
boys body is dragged down the steps and onto the nearby pavement 
twenty minutes later an ambulance arrives emanuele dies in a 
nearby hospital 
at 3 am thursday the bus crosses over into the netherlands 
and comes to a halt on the edge of a forest near the town of 
oldenzaal all hostages except for two women are freed 
supplied with another bmw the three bandits silke bischof and 
another hostage speed toward amsterdam before doubling back to west 
germany 
after getting bandages and medicines for the injured ms 
loeblich roesner drives the car into downtown cologne shortly 
after 1130 am he parks the shiny gray bmw near a pedestrian mall 
where a chilean folk music company continues a flute performance 
miss bischof an 18yearold court stenographer from bremen 
tells reporters shes all right 
im just afraid that the police will move in she says as 
degowski points a loaded revolver at her occasionally jamming it 
into her neck then something could happen and somebody will be 
killed again 
degowski nervously chainsmoking walks to a nearby cafe and 
orders a waitress to bring coffee to the waiting car she refuses 
so he brings it himself again no uniformed police are in sight 
roesner getting nervous jumps out of the car and frantically 
waves his gun around before speeding off just as undercover police 
are approaching 
two hours later the police catch up and a shootout erupts on a 
crowded highway near bonn 
during the melee one of the two gunmen shoots silke in the 
heart 
police capture degowski loeblich and roesner who has suffered 
a gunshot wound in the thigh the second hostage is taken to the 
hospital with a superficial bullet wound as police investigators 
swarm the area 
they just drove right into the trap says witness konrad 
anders 
