<TEXT>
north star foods inc of st charles minn 
has issued a voluntary nationwide recall of an estimated 200000 
pounds of turkey products and ham because they are undercooked the 
agriculture department said friday 
if eaten the undercooked turkey could cause salmonellosis a 
form of food poisoning and the ham could cause trichinosis which 
can be caused by microscopic parasitic worms in infected pork 
lester m crawford administrator of the departments food 
safety and inspection service said no illnesses have been reported 
the recalled products include turkey bologna ovencooked turkey 
breast white and dark turkey rolls cured turkey thigh meat 
cooked turkey drumstick and cooked ham 
these products are manufactured in bulk for slicing and are sold 
in 3 to 18pound packages primarily to delicatessens hospitals 
institutions hotels and other distributors that slice the product 
before using he said 
the turkey products can be identified by the brand name north 
star and bear the establishment code est p8191 inside the usda 
inspection seal on the label 
also being recalled are pioneer brand oven prepared turkey 
breast and emge brand oven prepared turkey breast with broth which 
are prepared by north star and distributed by emge packing co 
inc fort branch ind these products also bear the establishment 
code est p8191 inside the usda inspection seal 
the hams can be identified by the north star brand name and 
haave the code est 8191 inside the usda seal the hams weigh 9 
pounds 
officials said the recall applies only to products produced 
before aug 3 any consumer deli or institution holding these 
products should return them to the place of purchase 
crawford said that consumers who have bought such products 
without the original packaging from a delicatessen or other 
institution should ask the seller whether the product came from 
north star foods est p8191 or 8191 
salmonella bacteria may be present in turkeys at the time of 
slaughter and the consumption of undercooked or underprocessed 
products could cause salmonellosis common symptoms may include 
headache abdominal discomfort diarrhea and vomiting crawford 
said 
hogs may have living trichane organisms in their muscle tissues 
at the time of slaughter and if the organisms arent killed by 
proper cooking or processing the pork could cause trichinosis an 
uncommon but potentially serious infection he said 
</TEXT>
