investigating little and had interviewed more than 80 people 
he said he felt hed been hounded by the press and he just 
couldnt take it anymore said attorney camden hall a friend of 
little who spoke to him by telephone just minutes before the judge 
died it was too much pressure the hounding wouldnt stop 
he was not only driven into disgrace but to death said hal 
