admonished little the commission had received a complaint as early 
as 1981 from the king county prosecutors office that little was 
violating the code of judicial conduct by having outofcourt 
contact with juvenile offenders and the prosecutors office 
followed up with a second report in 1983 the times reported 
the commissions action was not made public until 1985 little 
had been reelected in 1984 
