misconduct that allegedly occurred before the commission was formed 
in december 1980 
the commissions chairman colfax attorney wesley a nuxoll 
said he thinks the commissions confidential proceedings are 
necessary to encourage people to come forward with complaints and 
speak freely about them 
he also said he would have reservations about modifying the rule 
against considering pre1980 cases and thinks it would be a 
serious mistake to make all complaints public 
