<TEXT>
i dont like to be reminded im getting old after 25 its 
all downhill leonard bernstein 1958 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
hes gone through life like a volcano erupting 
in a torrent of creative energy as constant as his chain of 
cigarettes and his dramatic bursts and artistic drive have not 
abated as he celebrates his 70th birthday 
leonard bernstein the 
composerconductorpianistteachertelevision celebrity will mark 
the aug 25 birthday with four nights of performances at the 
tanglewood music center in massachusetts where he once studied 
under the great conductor serge koussevitsky 
i havent slept very much in months the stocky 
whitehaired maestro said last week at tanglewood i have no 
further request of the fates except time to write my music 
ive got a lot of music to write 
bernstein whos thrilled millions around the world with his 
compositions his podium pirouettes and his more than 400 
recordings has been active as he approached this milestone year 
from may until december his schedule listed 63 conducting 
performances in 25 cities in 10 countries three were in moscow 
last month his first visit to the country of his parents in 29 
years 
the past year also has seen premieres of two bernstein 
compositions my twelve tone melody for irving berlins 100th 
birthday and jubilee games to celebrate the 50th anniversary 
of the israel philharmonic orchestra with which he has long been 
associated 
a decade ago bernsteins energy waned after the death of his 
wife chilean actress felicia montealegre and he slipped into 
months of depression but since then he has divided much of his 
time between his homes in new york and fairfield conn and 
austria where he has often appeared with the vienna philharmonic 
his life has been as dizzy a balancing act as his emotional 
style on the podium jabs contortions and leaps that have 
occasionally caused him to fall his style at the podium has been 
such a giggle that the music critic virgil thomson once said he 
shagged shimmied and believe it or not bumped 
bernstein himself has often maintained that conductors should be 
actors 
i dont mean that when the music is tragic youve got to act 
like barrymore in hamlet but you have to indicate to the 
orchestra by your body and your face which is all youve got what 
the shape of the phrase is he said if you dont use a baton 
you work harder because then your arm has to take its place 
bernstein was a wiry young man of 25 with bony face and dark 
wavy hair when he got the break that helped him become one of 
americas titans of classical music 
on nov 14 1943 he filled in at the last minute for an ailing 
bruno walter to conduct the new york philharmonic on a national 
radio broadcast the triumph of the orchestras newly appointed 
assistant conductor was big enough to join the world war ii 
headlines on the front page of the new york times 
i had no sleep no rehearsal a splitting headache 
bernstein recalled in a recent interview with life i walked on 
with an awful hangover and dont remember another thing until i 
heard a thunderous ovation 
bernstein has juggled careers as a composer and conductor his 
compositions range from the theatrical on the town west 
side story to chamber music 
in his compositions as well as his highly acclaimed televised 
series of young peoples concerts he skimmed the cream from 
classical music and pasteurized it for the american palate 
they write letters to me from the desert from montana from 
hundreds of miles off bernstein once said in an interview with 
the associated press theyve begun to enjoy music they arent 
scared of it any more they thought it was too much for them and 
ive helped convince them it isnt 
while bernsteins musical fame grew his celebrity blossomed 
media attention really focused when he threw became known as that 
party at lennys his starstudded fundraiser for the black 
panthers which was savaged by tom wolfe as radical chic 
yet he has been shrewd in marketing his career setting up 
amberson enterprises in 1969 to manage films tv specials and 
videocasettes of his performances 
born in lawrence mass to a middleclass russianjewish 
family bernstein got a late start in music he was 10 when his 
aunt clara gave the family an upright piano but he always had an 
ear for music recalled his mother jennie in bernstein a 
biography by joan peyser 
when he was 4 or 5 he would play an imaginary piano on his 
windowsill mrs bernstein said in the book when we finally 
got a piano he did what he now says he did made love to it all 
the time 
his father sam however hoped young lenny would join his 
beauty supply business bernstein persisted with piano lessons he 
went on to study under walter piston at harvard university and 
under fritz reiner at the curtis institute 
</TEXT>
