<TEXT>
during his harvard days he met conductor dimitri mitropoulis 
who recognized his genius and encouraged him to pursue conducting 
he also met aaron copland at a 1937 concert later that night at a 
party for coplands 37th birthday bernstein impressed the composer 
with an impromptu performance without the sheet music of his 
difficult piano variations 
with coplands help bernstein whose greatest works were for 
the stage pursued classical composition he had written 
jeremiah the first of his three symphonies before artur 
rodzinski appointed him his assistant at the philharmonic in 1943 
koussevitzky the boston symphonys influential music director 
and founder of tanglewood advised his student to pursue classical 
music but bernstein continued with popular music 
the year of his philharmonic appointment he wrote the ballet 
fancy free which was a success the plot about three sailors 
24hour shore leave in new york was adapted for broadways on 
the town winning five tony awards 
soon to come were his chamber opera trouble in tahiti the 
movie score for on the waterfront broadways wonderful 
town and candide and the immortal west side story the 
romeoandjuliet tale set amid the fire escapes and street gangs of 
manhattan in the late 1950s 
bernsteins successful substitution for walter also put him in 
great demand as a conductor he left the philharmonic to be guest 
conductor at major orchestras performing in the united states and 
abroad in 1953 he became the first american to conduct at milans 
famed la scala opera house leading diva maria callas in 
cherubinis opera medea 
in 1957 the year he completed west side story bernstein 
joined mitropoulis as codirector of the new york philharmonic and 
the following year became the orchestras first americanborn 
director 
during his 11year tenure bernstein led the orchestra on tours 
of south america europe and asia and on numerous national 
television appearances in which he explained classical music to 
americans young and old his tv appearances which included the 
young peoples concerts won 11 emmy awards 
bernstein has had his critics who over the years called him 
overrated as a composer and thrashed his ballet style on the podium 
bernstein rose vertically a la nijinsky and hovered there a 
good 15 seconds the new york times critic harold schonberg once 
wrote 
but later on the occasion of bernsteins 1000th performance 
with the philharmonic on dec 15 1971 schonberg wrote at this 
time it is only right to put reservations aside and salute 
bernstein for what he did and even for what he tried to do 
bernstein was a figure that no conductor in history has matched 
among those scheduled to participate at this weeks concerts 
with the boston symphony orchestra are his son alexander 33 a 
teacher and daughter nina a 26yearold actress he also has 
another daughter jaime thomas 36 a rock musician and the mother 
of bernsteins only grandchild 
others include conductors seiji ozawa john williams michael 
tilson thomas and lauren bacall phyllis newman betty comden 
adolph green van cliburn yoyo ma elizabeth taylor publisher 
malcolm forbes and beverly sills who will be host tickets were 
selling for up to 5000 
despite the ado bernstein dreads facing his eighth decade 
everybody is much more excited about this 70th birthday 
business than i am he told the miami herald in june id like 
to ignore it 
in fact that number is just not in my vocabulary i hate 
those pictures of myself with wrinkles white hair and glasses i 
look like the little old winemaker 
</TEXT>
