<TEXT>
whirlpool corps plan to acquire a majority 
stake in the appliance division of dutch electronics giant nv 
philips guarantees the company the top slot among appliance makers 
around the globe 
whirlpool announced thursday it will pay philips 470 million 
for 53 percent of a joint venture company that will develop 
manufacture and market major appliances under philips brand names 
the new company will employ 14000 people from the present 
philips division and will have annual sales of about 2 billion 
boosting whirpools annual revenue to about 6 billion the 
companies said in a statement 
whirlpool a close second domestically to general electric co 
long has sought to branch out of the relatively mature 12 billion 
us appliance market the company is affiliated with appliance 
concerns in canada brazil mexico and india but not in the 
lucrative european market represented by philips 
they desperately needed a wellestablished brand which 
philips is said charles ryan a first vice president at the 
investment firm merrill lynch amp co 
philips is the worlds largest television maker and europes 
biggest electronics company 
whirlpools move mirrors deals by other manufacturing companies 
seeking to rid themselves of weaker businesses and focus on markets 
where they can be major players 
last year ge became one of the worlds top medical equipment 
concerns after swapping its consumer electronics business for 
thomson sas medical equipment operations thomson in turn 
strengthened its role in consumer electronics 
also last year philips acquired the 42 percent of north 
american philips corp it did not already own to solidify its 
strength in the television lighting radio and appliance markets 
here 
you cant be everything to everybody said gerrit jeelof 
executive vice president and vice chairman of the board of 
management of philips 
speaking at a press conference here jeelof said the whirlpool 
venture would free management resources to concentrate on philips 
core electronics businesses such as semiconductors and the coming 
generation of highdefinition television 
last year philips discussed a joint venture with whirlpool and 
britains general electric co which is unrelated to the us 
company of the same name those talks fell through because of 
uncertain economic conditions following the stock market crash and 
a weak dollar 
but they parted very friendly and this year the dollar has 
come back up relative to the dutch guilder so talks were 
reactivated merrill lynchs ryan said 
whirlpool will pay philips 350 million for a 53 percent stake 
in the joint venture and 120 million more if the venture continues 
beyond three years whirlpool has an option to acquire the 
remainder of the philips division for which it would pay 470 
million instead of the 120 million 
the new company will be based in the netherlands and will market 
washers dryers refrigerators freezers stoves microwave ovens 
and dishwashers around the world but primarily in europe 
appliances will be sold under the philips bauknecht and ignis 
brand names 
whirlpool could take advantage of philips expertise in 
convection cooking and gas cooking while the european joint 
venture could benefit from whirlpools strength in products such as 
dishwashers air conditioners and clothes dryers that are beginning 
to catch on in europe said david r whitwam whirlpools chairman 
president and chief executive officer 
whirlpool stock rose 12 cents to 2575 a share in new york 
stock exchange trading 
whirlpool based in benton harbor mich manufactures and 
markets a range of home appliances under the whirlpool kitchenaid 
and roper brand names the company which employs about 31000 
people and has annual sales of about 42 billion also is a major 
supplier to sears roebuck amp co of kenmore products 
the joint venture is the latest in a string of consolidations in 
the appliance industry 
earlier this year whirlpool engaged in a bidding war with ge 
over the appliance maker roper corp ge ultimately acquired roper 
and its manufacturing facilities but whirlpool struck a deal to 
gain the roper brand name 
other major appliance mergers in recent years include maytag 
corps acquisition of magic chef co and the acquisition of white 
consolidated industries by swedens electrolux ab 
last month philips announced its profit fell 44 percent in the 
second quarter an unexpectedly poor performance that the company 
blamed on an onslaught of competition from southeast asia and 
losses on foreign currencies 
philips hinted then that it was about to take a major step to 
raise cash such as a big joint venture or sale of a large part of 
the company 
philips whose annual sales have topped 25 billion has been 
cutting costs at its european factories and moving more production 
to lowercost areas including the united states in the past seven 
months it has laid off 6000 european employees and has promised at 
least 4000 more cuts 
